reviews_data.review_text: i love this library

Great library and friendly staff, I always enjoy my time here! Currently they are having a bottle cap donation box and summer reading program too so I thought I would share what some of the raffle prizes are for 2025

I love this library and have been coming here for years, I'm 15 and often sit in the teens section with my brother doing schoolwork, or drawing. Recently, there's been this older man that I'm assuming was Recently hired, keeps coming over and eyeing us, following us, and talking to us. At first it was harmless, just asking how our days were, but today he was really rude and creepy, hovering over us constantly, asking if we were really teenagers. He said we were being loud, so we quieted down. We've never had complaints from other librarians and all the staff know us by name so if there's an issue they always say so, he's the first to have a problem with it. Im going to tone it down, but he gives me weird vibes.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi! We're sorry your experience was negative. We have relayed this information to the branch manager and are looking into it, but we believe the staff member you encountered is our temporary security and he will be in the building patrolling regularly to make sure the library is safe and that there are no adults in the teen area without reason. If you have any further concerns, please reach out to us at library@cabarruscounty.us.

reviews_data.review_text: Wonderful library with helpful staff.  You’ll learn lots!

Great selection of books! They have a teenager section with seating and a great selection of anime! The upstairs has a decently large area for children away from the adult sections! I enjoy going to this library especially since the librarians are always nice and very helpful!

1) Sat in the teen section were there were no teens at all ....a lady comes to me and says you have to move ...i said i thought the rule was if teens come then you will be asked to yield to them and she said no so basically had to leave and still no one sitting there

2) they said they only have one quiet study room ...i said cool they said they don't have an opening till 3pm i go upstairs and NOONE is in that room

3) when i find a new seat to be in a lady comes up to me and says no foam cups.....i said lady it's water ....and she says that the tools and give me a bottle of water

This is not a library this a homeless shelter masquerading as a library who have librarians who are petty and naggy about having water in your cups but let homeless people sleep and have loud music
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hello! We're sorry you had a less than optimal experience. Ensuring that every member of our community can come and find a comfortable space at the library is our staff's top priority. We do have a Patron Conduct Policy that we apply equally across the board regarding food, beverages, and adult usage of children's areas other than for the purposes of browsing books, which is available on our website.

reviews_data.review_text: Good library and selection. Friendly and helpful  staff. Only issue is work going on in the street infront of the library due to which the entrance becomes little confusing every time
Found a new Greenway! I have been searching for a new place to walk. It’s very pleasant and quiet. Recommend it for a peaceful walk in the park.

The librarians here are always super helpful. My youngest struggles with reading and gets frustrated easily, but the staff there were super friendly and found several books at her reading level that she genuinely enjoyed reading.
Excellent library! In spite of homeless presence.Lin was great and so helpful! A real asset
I love this library. The staff is absolutely wonderful and they have a great selection of books.

This Library is essentially a homeless shelter. It’s constantly overrun with a homeless population that loiter, litter and use profanity all day inside and out.  Most tax paying local citizens don’t want to utilize this Library due to this issue. This is not a good thing for our downtown.
Nice folks. Very helpful.
Love this library. Friendly staff and a nice collection of books.

This is a homeless shelter, not a library.

I travel a lot for my job and I frequently stop at libraries in order to get some work done. I decided to check out this location today. I wish I hadn’t.

As I drove through Concord to the library, the town seem charming. But when I pulled into the library lot, I saw a convention of sketchy people surrounding the entrance.

Having run that gauntlet, inside the building, there were very few tables that were not occupied by the homeless.

About half an hour into my visit, I was approached by a librarian, who condescendingly scolded me about having a drink with me. Very specifically, she had a problem with it being soda. She said that water would have been fine. She told me I either had to throw it away or leave.

As I left the building in order to put my drink in the car, I did see two signs on the front door that I had not previously noticed that did say that food and drinks were not allowed. However, it said nothing about water being permitted. Only that all drinks were prohibited.

I returned my seat and stayed for approximately another three hours. During that time, I noticed that many of the homeless people who were not napping, were openly eating. The man beside me was eating McDonald’s while cutting his fingernails. And a patron using the library’s computer had a Burger King cup right beside the keyboard.

I don’t understand why the no food or drink policy applies to normal library patrons, but not homeless people. Of all the people I saw eating and drinking, I was the only one who was admonished. Whatever the reason for such a policy to exist, one would suspect might be to prevent damage to the library’s property but this doesn’t explain why it’s OK to have a drink at the computer, but I’m not allowed to have a drink at a table with my own laptop.

As I left for the day, I noticed the number of security cameras around the building, and the no loitering signs, and the signs to keep your vehicle locked because of break-ins and that they are not responsible if that does occur.

Frankly, this library serves as and caters to the homeless, who are in need of a shelter, rather than as a library for patrons.

This was a very unwelcoming welcome to Concord and I will not return.

Went to this library with a friend and our
Kids and three homeless men walked out .. we walked inside and there were more homeless inside and outside / needs to be updated also saw zero section for kids. I doubt we will be back . Very sad for the homeless but this isn’t a shelter

Love this library! The staff is always friendly and helpful. The summer reading programs are fun for both kids and adults. The puzzle exchange is a brilliant idea and my family uses it frequently. Wonderful library all around!
Absolutely wonderful staff!!  Angela, in the children’s department, was very helpful with different programs and different types of learning mediums for my 7yr old and 4yr old.
A great little library. The staff are very friendly  and they usually have something going on for the family.

Twice now, the librarians have helped me sift through YouTube tutorials and relearn excel. I cannot say enough about how much their help improved my life.

Then later when I was checking out, I got some tips about the author that were informative and cute...

You know how cool it is to find someone who has read the same books as you and can talk out it??

Every time I come here I leave feeling welcome & served.

Best in town.
Closed 25 mins before scheduled time, and refused to answer the phone. Very disappointed with their lack of professionalism.
I don't understand why they allow people to talk so much in this library.
Nice, quiet, organized place to study inside or outside.

What a fantastic organization. As a parent of 2 I am so thankful to have such wonderful programs available for the kids. The entire staff is welcoming to all and the ladies who run story time are the best.

The staff is very helpful and friendly. They were all eagered to assist me with my children's reading questions. They also offered additional information for my advance reader and my reader who struggles. Super helpful upstairs and downstairs
Nice place to hang out and learn something

I was in there yesterday. There was an incident that happened and I know that anywhere else they would have called the police and had them escort out. Instead this lady showed sympathy and empathy and did the right thing. These days it's hard to find that. This lady is the type of person that makes me proud to be American. This library branch has the best people working there.

I am a visitor from GA & this is HANDS DOWN the best library I’ve been to & the main staff @ the computer center (a man) was EXTREMELY helpful & patient. Very friendly staff & VERY advanced system in regards to paying for printing & scanning document. Highly recommend 1000/10
I absolutely love this library. The workers are more than willing to help you.
Thanks so much to John. I had  a computer class this morning with John  and when i left I actually felt smarter  then when i can in . He was a wealth of info. Thanks again
Great for kids and enough of a selection for even the most voracious reader
Going to this library is always great. The people are always wonderful. Checking out is quick and easy. I can always find what I'm looking for.

Our family loves this library and our children have grown up using all their amazing services. Currently their favorite is to put books on hold so the books are ready for easy pick up. The staff are always friendly and helpful.
Today my wife and I set up ebook accounts; and found I can even use it to read on my Kindle.😊

We love the library in downtown Concord.  They are accommodating and very helpful. If you can’t find a book at their location they will find it at any of the libraries in Cabarrus county. My son loves the preschool story time as well he has the best time reading stories with them and singing songs.  They are awesome!
Best place in town. Friendly librarians. Will order any book I ask for.

If you enjoy the experience of noisy "patrons" coming out of elevators in a standing room only environment, this is the library for you. Watch as the librarians allow people to come pouring out of the elevators joking with other "patrons", loudly talk on their phones, and often times laughing loudly to themselves as you attempt to concentrate on research or studies. Good luck finding a desk or comfortable seating in general. This library has been slowly taking out desks to push away the homeless population in the area that apparently this staff is not intellectually capable of handling.

If you donate to this library, I would urge you to reconsider, as that money would be much more useful as kindling for a fire in your back yard.
Mian branch of the Cabarrus County Public library. Ample parking at the back and very helpful staff. Holds lots of events for kids and adults.
Nice and quiet, Good for studying and reading
Staff are super friendly and helpful. Always clean and easy to navigate.
It is a great public library! It is always clean and the staff are always friendly.
Best librarians in the kids section, they make excellent suggestions for kids
Nice clean great book selection! And helpful staff. Thankful for a library!
Awesome staff, love the ease of everything
Wonderful library! I’ve been bringing my kids for more than 6 years to the library organized work shops and mornings fun for toddlers. The kids love it and so do I.
I just went for the quiet atmosphere

We go to many different librarys and this library is the absolute worst when it comes to the amount of dvds you can check out. Even during the times of covid. Or when those who have special needs just don't wanna put that 7th dvd down. You should be able to make  exceptions at times. Rules to the extreme upstarts in the kid area the workers are always decently loud when in the work room when they talk amongst themselves but yet you can't answer your phone and talk extra quiet. There was nobody in there but me and my client who is special needs so I can't just step out and leave him I have to keep my eyes on him the entire time. Yall need to learn some freaking compassion.
Just wish they had hand sanitizer
Very nice people working there. Great library
Love the curbside pickup service they've implemented.
Staff are delightful!
Very safe! Drop off books outside in the bin call for curbside pickup if you don't want to go inside. If you feel comfortable going inside, they have a new self service check out that works great 🙂
I needed to print documents for a deadline. Thanks library staff for all your help.
I am new to area and this is a very nice clean location. I like fact that I can go here when I need to fax something too and staff is very helpful.
This place is incredible! Very nice staff!
Really good books and Computers work
Staff always willing to assist.
Five stars to the very helpful staffs!

Amazing library with a lot to offer for the children. We go to story time on Tuesdays and Janey is amazing! Only thing that is a bummer is that you cannot print in color and there are no fax machines. Otherwise, amazing staff and awesome library!
Very good library. it is nice,its clean and has everthing thing you would want at a library.
Great place
It is amazing
Amazing library, nice staff, lot of choice and such a great kid department!
If you're looking for some peace and quiet away from home, this public library has just that. It's a great place to study or enjoy a great book.

Amazing place. Never enjoyed myself as much as I did in a library before. They have a kids area with computers for early start to the digital world. With fun interactive games for young kids. Definitely coming here again. Thought the rain had messed up our chance of having fun but it was a cozy indoor experience that was impeccable.
Always good about holding books for you.

Excellent selection and knowledgable staff.  And it's not only books - internet access, audio books, periodicals and movies are also available.

Great library with great staff too. They are helpful and polite. I think they have a good collection of books too.
Parking too is good, especially considering it is in the center of Concord.
Clean and organised.  Staff was very helpful with a couple research projects
Well ran library with courteous knowledgeable staff
Very polite and nice staff. It's a very well run library
Awesome library, love going there with my kids. And its 5 mins from my home.
